<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- craft_your_research_q.html -->
<html lang="en">
  <head>
  	<title>Determine your approach</title>
    <link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:300italic,400italic,700italic,300,400,700);" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/css/main.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/css/font-awesome.min.css" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.12.4/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
   <form action="/determine_your_approach" method="post">
          <div class="container-fluid">
          <div class="row">
              <div class="col-xs-12">
                  <div class="tool-header">
                      <h1 class="tool-title"> Determine your approach</h1>
                      <div class="intro">
                          <p>
                              The Ed Tech RCE Wizard can use one of two approaches to answer your research question. To determine the right one we need you to answer the following questions:
                          </p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
              </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
              <div class="tool-questions">
                  <div class="step-header container">
                      <div data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#A">
                          <h2 class="clickable">
                              <i class="fa fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                              A. Are you already using this technology?
                          </h2>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="A" class="row  collapse">
                      <div class="col-xs-7">
                          <div class="step-action">
                              <select required name="Prob_Appr_A">
                                  <%
                                  var options = [ "Yes", "No"];
                                  for ( var i = 0; i < options.length; i++ )
                                  {
                                  var selected;
                                  if (probAppr) { selected = ( probAppr.Prob_Appr_A== options[i] ) ? "selected" : "";}
                                  %>
                                  <option value="<%=options[ i ] %>" <%=selected %> ><%=options[ i ] %></option><%
                                  }
                                  %>

                              </select>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="step-header container">
                      <div data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#B">
                          <h2 class="clickable"><i class="fa fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> B. Who are the technology users?</h2>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="B" class="row collapse">
                      <div class="col-xs-7">
                          <div>
                               <p> Ex. if you are interested in testing an educational technology that students can use to learn math, and you can observe test scores at the student level, your unit of observation is a student.
                               </p>
                          </div>
                          <div class="step-action">
                             
                              <select required name="Prob_Appr_B" id="q8">
                                  <%
                                    var options = [ "students", "schools", "teachers", "parents", "other"];
                                    for ( var i = 0; i < options.length; i++ )
                                    {
                                        var selected;
                                            if (probAppr) { selected = ( probAppr.Prob_Appr_B == options[i] ) ? "selected" : "";}
                                        %><option value="<%=options[ i ] %>" <%=selected %> ><%=options[ i ] %></option><%
                                    }
                                  %>
                              
                              </select>
                              <div id="other-specify" hidden="true">
                                <p>Please specify:</p>
                                <input type="text" id="otherSpecify"></input>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                  </div>
               
                  <div class="step-header container">
                      <div data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#C">
                          <h2 class="clickable"><i class="fa fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> C. Are/Will you using/use the technology?</h2>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="C" class="row collapse">
                      <div class="col-xs-7">
                          <div class="step-action">
                              <select required name="Prob_Appr_C">
                                  <%
                                  var options = [ "Yes", "No"];
                                  for ( var i = 0; i < options.length; i++ )
                                  {
                                  var selected;
                                  if (probAppr) { selected = ( probAppr.Prob_Appr_C == options[i] ) ? "selected" : "";}
                                  %>
                                  <option value="<%=options[ i ] %>" <%=selected %> ><%=options[ i ] %></option><%
                                  }
                                  %>

                              </select>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                      <p><b>Conclusion:</b><br>
                      Based on your answer we will guide you through a <span data-toggle="tooltip" title="Lorem Ipsum" class='tooltip-gr'>matched comparison design</span>. This is a <span data-toggle="tooltip" title="Lorem Ipsum" class='tooltip-gr'>quasi-experimental design</span>. To compare apples to apples, this quasi-experimental design will identify a <span data-toggle="tooltip" title="Lorem Ipsum" class='tooltip-gr'>comparison group</span> with similar characteristics to the <span class="section-b-header">subjects</span> using the technology that you want to test.
                      </p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                     <button type="submit" class="btn btn-warning btn-lg">Next</button>
                  </div>
              </div>
          </div>
      </div>
      <div>
          <input class="hidden" name="userid" value="<%= probAppr.userid %>" />
          <input class="hidden" name="_id" value="<%= probAppr._id %>" />
      </div>
   </form>
    
    <script src='/static/js/custom.js'></script>
  </body>
</html>
